# Quality Gates

## Must Pass All
All of the following validation gates must pass for a build or migration to be considered successful:

- All .csproj files validated (RULE #24)
- All DLL references use HintPath (RULE #4)
- All projects build successfully (RULE #30)
- All code warnings fixed (RULE #26)
- No data state in Razor.cs (RULE #27)
- No R_FrontGlobalVar in ViewModels (RULE #9)
- No Logger/Activity in Common (RULE #3, Template #1, #2)
- No modified SQL/SP (constraints.mdc)
- R_BackGlobalVar used correctly for IClientHelper (RULE #14)
- Streaming context optimized (RULE #29)
- Query logging implemented before all SqlExecQueryAsync, SqlExecNonQueryAsync calls (RULE #33)
- Streaming pattern NO parameters enforced (RULE #32, #37)
- Front project .csproj uses Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Razor (RULE #38)
- R_Button uses ChildContent pattern (RULE #39)
- R_Lookup wrapped in R_ItemLayout auto='true' (RULE #40)
- Column layout validation passed (RULE #41)
- Using statements organized in _Imports.razor (RULE #42)
- MessageBoxService implemented correctly (RULE #43)
- Localizer integration complete (RULE #44)
- Error messages from resources (RULE #45)
- Behavioral parity confirmed

